.TH "ti_bandgap_set_continuous_mode" 9 "ti_bandgap_set_continuous_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_bandgap_set_continuous_mode \- One time enabling of continuous mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ti_bandgap_set_continuous_mode
.BI "(struct ti_bandgap *bgp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bgp" 12
pointer to struct ti_bandgap
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call this function only if HAS(MODE_CONFIG) is set. As this driver may
be used for junction temperature monitoring, it is desirable that the
sensors are operational all the time, so that alerts are generated
properly.
.SH "RETURN"
0
